cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the problem of fitting geometric primitives to 3D point cloud data using a neural network approach. This problem is related to computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR) as it involves processing 3D data. The use of a neural network also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the application of this technique to downstream tasks such as robotics (cs.RO) is also mentioned in the abstract.
